{
  "texts": [
    "In line with this, Coda-Forno et al.",
    "(2023) found that using emotive language in prompts can lead to more bias in the model's responses.",
    "Furthermore, ChatGPT (OpenAI, 2022) robustly responded to an anxiety questionnaire with higher anxiety scores for the model than for humans.",
    "Furthermore, there is evidence that LLMs are able to display empathy (Sorin et al., 2023).",
    "After the stellar rise of ChatGPT (OpenAI, 2022) in late 2022, a proliferation of LLMs could be witnessed as large tech companies such as Google (Anil et al., 2023; Ghahramani, 2023; Hsiao, 2023; Pichai and Hassabis, 2024), Apple (McKinzie et al., 2024), Meta (Meta, 2023a), and Amazon all raced to release competitive largescale models."
  ]
}